Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nuremberg (DPA) -- At the German-Czech border 
checkpoint of Furth im Wald-Schafberg police and customs 
officials seized 90 kg of heroin. The drugs were hidden in a 
refrigerated truck from Turkey. According to first findings, 
the cargo was destined for the Netherlands, the joint 
investigating group of police and customs anounced in Nuremberg 
on Tuesday. 

